race.description: Ladies Day Sunday 2 Nov Maiden Plate
race.comment: PONTEVEDRA (12) was well in commission on debut last start over 1200m at Newcastle but after racing handy to the corner could not go on with the job. Not much depth to this field so with some natural improvement he looks tough to beat. NULKABA STAR (2) travelled on the speed and was in for the fight but found a couple marginally better when resuming over 1000m at this track last time out. Far better placed out to today's journey. Looms as the obvious threat. EDDIE'S CHARM (7) settled at the back of the field and was never in the hunt first-up over 1250m at Newcastle. Locally trained mare who might be worth another chance with a couple of key gear changes for this. THINK PI (5) led but capitulated here at this trip most recently. Fitter now and can offer a bit more resistance. First starter SOULS COMPANION (4) hasn't set the world on fire at the trials but there has been early market confidence so keep him safe.
